OL,6,FMr and Mrs Evans, of High Brigham,
OL,7,Fnear Cockermouth, inseparable since
OL,8,Fmeeting at Oxford University and known
OL,9,Fby friends as "PatnGareth" ` were
OL,10,Fheading to church at the time of the
OL,11,Ffatal crash.
OL,13,FMr Evans had worked as an industrial
OL,14,Fchemist at Sellafield, while his wife
OL,15,Ftaught maths. They were long-term
OL,16,Fmembers of St John's Church,
OL,17,FWorkington, and integral to
OL,18,Fbellringing, choirs and music groups.
